I wasn't built that way.

251
00:13:15,504 --> 00:13:16,755
I just...

252
00:13:17,714 --> 00:13:19,632
I feel like there's always
something inside of me

253
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:20,717
holding me back.

254
00:13:34,105 --> 00:13:35,106
["Boy" playing]

255
00:13:46,284 --> 00:13:48,410
No, no, no.

256
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:49,496
<i>♪ Uh-huh ♪</i>

257
00:13:50,497 --> 00:13:51,498
Come on.

258
00:13:56,211 --> 00:13:57,212
<i>♪ Uh-huh ♪</i>

259
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:01,465
Okay, get up, bitch.

260
00:14:01,466 --> 00:14:03,467
- Get up! Come on!
- No. Oh, God.

261
00:14:03,468 --> 00:14:05,345
- [Eli] Come on!
- [Patrick] That's right.

262
00:14:06,012 --> 00:14:07,221
- [Eli] You too.
- What the fuck?

263
00:14:07,222 --> 00:14:08,597
Put that phone away
and get up.

264
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:10,266
- Okay.
- [Eli] Get your asses up.

265
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:12,185
- [Patrick] Come on.
- [Eli] Come on!

266
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:01,359
Iris, what are you doing?

267
00:15:23,131 --> 00:15:24,299
[groans]

268
00:15:25,884 --> 00:15:28,178
[breathes heavily] Ah!

269
00:15:29,638 --> 00:15:30,889
[grunting]

270
00:15:42,275 --> 00:15:44,027
I'm so glad we did this.

271
00:15:45,737 --> 00:15:47,739
Being here with you
is just perfect.

272
00:15:48,990 --> 00:15:49,991
Uh-huh.

273
00:15:51,534 --> 00:15:55,538
I'm sorry if I was being weird
or mopey earlier.

274
00:15:58,708 --> 00:16:03,379
I just want you
to be happy, Josh. That's all.

275
00:16:03,380 --> 00:16:05,048
Iris, go to sleep.

276
00:16:08,510 --> 00:16:10,303
[water running]

277
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:23,566
It's such a gorgeous day out.

278
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:25,902
[Josh] Uh, what's the weather?

279
00:16:26,444 --> 00:16:28,028
It's currently 72 degrees

280
00:16:28,029 --> 00:16:30,781
with an 83% chance
of rain in the evening.

281
00:16:30,782 --> 00:16:32,367
[Josh chuckles]
It never gets old.

282
00:16:35,286 --> 00:16:37,664
- [water stops running]
- [spits, sighs]

283
00:16:38,748 --> 00:16:41,333
- [Iris] You almost ready?
- Oh, I'm sorry, babe.

284
00:16:41,334 --> 00:16:42,876
I think I need
some time to shower

285
00:16:42,877 --> 00:16:44,545
and pound
a few gallons of coffee.

286
00:16:44,546 --> 00:16:45,879
Why don't, uh--

287
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:48,006
Why don't you head
down there by yourself?

288
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:49,592
But it was your idea.

289
00:16:50,260 --> 00:16:53,262
You said you wanted a nice,
relaxing morning by the lake.

290
00:16:53,263 --> 00:16:56,098
I know, but that's before the
hangover caught up with me.

291
00:16:56,099 --> 00:16:58,435
Last night was a lot.

292
00:16:59,477 --> 00:17:00,979
You had fun though, right?

293
00:17:02,313 --> 00:17:03,940
Of course I did, Beep-Boop.

294
00:17:04,941 --> 00:17:06,276
Last night was incredible.

295
00:17:19,998 --> 00:17:21,416
You want me to wait?

296
00:17:22,542 --> 00:17:24,794
We could
make the shower for two.

297
00:17:27,088 --> 00:17:29,382
Nah, no, no.
That's okay. Um...

298
00:17:30,425 --> 00:17:31,509
You go on ahead.

299
00:17:32,385 --> 00:17:34,596
Enjoy as much of this
gorgeous day as you can.

300
00:17:36,931 --> 00:17:38,348
- Okay.
- [chuckles] Yeah.

301
00:17:38,349 --> 00:17:39,559
- Hmm.
- [sighs]

302
00:18:24,395 --> 00:18:26,147
[birds chirping]

303
00:19:12,944 --> 00:19:14,445
[Sergey speaking Russian]

304
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,409
Sorry?

305
00:19:20,410 --> 00:19:21,911
Means "good morning."

306
00:19:22,871 --> 00:19:24,247
Oh, yes.

307
00:19:25,290 --> 00:19:26,748
<i>Dobroe utro</i> to you too.

308
00:19:26,749 --> 00:19:29,710
Hey, your Russian is not bad.

309
00:19:29,711 --> 00:19:33,380
It is not good,
but also it is not bad.

310
00:19:33,381 --> 00:19:34,716
[both chuckle]

311
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:37,343
Nice view.

312
00:19:43,641 --> 00:19:44,766
[speaking Russian]

313
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:45,935
To love.

314
00:19:47,645 --> 00:19:48,646
[Sergey slurps]

315
00:19:54,611 --> 00:19:55,694
Mmm.

316
00:19:55,695 --> 00:19:56,778
You like?

317
00:19:56,779 --> 00:19:59,282
I think I'm actually going to
head back inside.

318
00:20:00,491 --> 00:20:01,491
So soon?

319
00:20:01,492 --> 00:20:02,951
Yeah...

320
00:20:02,952 --> 00:20:04,661
Josh wasn't feeling great
this morning,

321
00:20:04,662 --> 00:20:06,121
so I think I should
check in on him.

322
00:20:06,122 --> 00:20:08,957
Josh is big boy.
He can take care of himself.

323
00:20:08,958 --> 00:20:10,960
Stay. Keep Sergey company.

324
00:20:12,587 --> 00:20:14,464
I really think I should
see him.

325
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:17,634
You...

326
00:20:19,052 --> 00:20:20,553
like lake house, yes?

327
00:20:22,388 --> 00:20:23,388
Yeah.

328
00:20:23,389 --> 00:20:26,016
You enjoy your time here?

329
00:20:26,017 --> 00:20:28,226
Mm-hmm. Yeah, very much.

330
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:32,064
Then as guest, please stay.

331
00:20:32,065 --> 00:20:34,484
Keep this old Russian man
company.

332
00:20:37,612 --> 00:20:39,696
- Okay.
- Wonderful.

333
00:20:39,697 --> 00:20:40,782
Mmm.

334
00:20:50,917 --> 00:20:52,919
Oh. [sniffs]

335
00:20:54,379 --> 00:20:55,380
You mind?

336
00:20:56,589 --> 00:20:58,465
Just back and shoulders.

337
00:20:58,466 --> 00:21:00,384
- It's tough to reach.
- Oh.

338
00:21:00,385 --> 00:21:02,428
Don't want to get too tan.

339
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:13,606
[Iris] Okay.

340
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:17,568
Mmm.

341
00:21:21,072 --> 00:21:23,115
And shoulders, please.

342
00:21:23,116 --> 00:21:24,367
Okay.

343
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:32,291
[Sergey inhales sharply]

344
00:21:39,257 --> 00:21:40,383
What are you doing?

345
00:21:42,176 --> 00:21:45,388
It's not problem.
This Kat's idea.

346
00:21:45,930 --> 00:21:47,890
She tell Sergey
you are down here.

347
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:49,851
Give Sergey permission.

348
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,145
Let go of my hand, please.

349
00:21:53,146 --> 00:21:56,023
This is what you do, yes?

350
00:21:56,024 --> 00:21:58,735
This is what you are for.

351
00:22:01,779 --> 00:22:03,197
- [kisses] Mmm.
- Please.

352
00:22:03,948 --> 00:22:05,074
Please stop.

353
00:22:06,534 --> 00:22:07,576
[Josh chuckling]

354
00:22:07,577 --> 00:22:09,077
[Eli] I was drunk.
I mean, you--

355
00:22:09,078 --> 00:22:10,120
[Eli] Last night,
it was crazy.

356
00:22:10,121 --> 00:22:11,163
[Josh]
You were extremely drunk.

357
00:22:11,164 --> 00:22:13,165
You were drunk too.
Like, more drunk than I got.

358
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:14,875
I don't really get drunk.
It's like this gift.

359
00:22:14,876 --> 00:22:16,793
Like, people get bloated
and stuff, and not me.

360
00:22:16,794 --> 00:22:18,920
- Like, never happens.
- Never get bloated.

361
00:22:18,921 --> 00:22:20,964
Never. It's like I could drink
and do whatever I want.

362
00:22:20,965 --> 00:22:23,175
- It's like you get dehydrated.
- Yeah, just, like--

363
00:22:23,176 --> 00:22:24,510
What the fuck?

364
00:22:25,386 --> 00:22:26,678
[Josh] Oh, shit.

365
00:22:26,679 --> 00:22:29,557
- Iris, what the fuck?
- [Iris whimpers]

366
00:22:31,517 --> 00:22:32,934
I didn't mean to. He--

367
00:22:32,935 --> 00:22:34,019
[Josh breathes heavily]

368
00:22:34,020 --> 00:22:36,147
He forced himself on me.

369
00:22:36,689 --> 00:22:37,690
Who did?

370
00:22:38,941 --> 00:22:39,942
Sergey?

371
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:42,360
Mmm.

372
00:22:42,361 --> 00:22:43,612
Please.

373
00:22:43,613 --> 00:22:46,365
Sergey just want little taste.
[kisses]

374
00:22:50,036 --> 00:22:51,954
I just wanted him to stop.

375
00:22:53,581 --> 00:22:55,917
Oh, God. Sergey.

376
00:22:58,961 --> 00:23:02,589
Iris. Hey, look at me. Look
at me. Talk me through it.

377
00:23:02,590 --> 00:23:03,758
What happened?

378
00:23:04,509 --> 00:23:06,302
[breathes shakily] I--

379
00:23:07,512 --> 00:23:09,597
[kissing]

380
00:23:10,473 --> 00:23:11,557
I said stop!

381
00:23:15,895 --> 00:23:17,313
I didn't have a choice.

382
00:23:25,613 --> 00:23:26,697
Sergey?

383
00:23:28,157 --> 00:23:29,158
[groans]

384
00:23:35,706 --> 00:23:36,707
[speaking Russian]

385
00:23:37,708 --> 00:23:39,876
[Sergey grunting]

386
00:23:39,877 --> 00:23:42,003
- [grunting]
- [speaking Russian]

387
00:23:42,004 --> 00:23:45,132
He wouldn't let go.
He was choking me, Josh.

388
00:23:45,133 --> 00:23:46,633
[both grunting]

389
00:23:46,634 --> 00:23:47,844
[speaking Russian]

390
00:23:49,011 --> 00:23:50,262
And then I--

391
00:23:50,263 --> 00:23:51,847
And then you what, Iris?
Then you what?

392
00:23:51,848 --> 00:23:53,141
[both grunting]

393
00:23:56,102 --> 00:23:57,060
[Sergey grunting]

394
00:23:57,061 --> 00:23:58,186
[Iris]
<i>He was trying to kill me,</i>

395
00:23:58,187 --> 00:23:59,396
<i>and the only thing
I could think about</i>

396
00:23:59,397 --> 00:24:00,564
was that if he did kill me,

397
00:24:00,565 --> 00:24:02,149
I'd never get to
see you again,

398
00:24:02,150 --> 00:24:04,860
and that hurt so much more
than the pain of being choked!

399
00:24:04,861 --> 00:24:06,403
I wouldn't let that happen.

400
00:24:06,404 --> 00:24:07,779
I couldn't let him take me
away from you.

401
00:24:07,780 --> 00:24:09,781
I love you so much!

402
00:24:09,782 --> 00:24:11,159
Iris, go to sleep.

403
00:24:17,123 --> 00:24:19,333
[Iris humming]

404
00:24:22,628 --> 00:24:24,380
[Josh, muffled] Okay.
Don't forget her ankles, okay?

405
00:24:24,881 --> 00:24:26,047
[Patrick, muffled] Okay.

406
00:24:26,048 --> 00:24:27,549
Are you sure
this is gonna hold?

407
00:24:27,550 --> 00:24:29,092
[Josh, normal]
Yeah, no, it's fine.

408
00:24:29,093 --> 00:24:30,552
She's not superhuman
or anything.

409
00:24:30,553 --> 00:24:32,763
She's only as strong
as they want her to be.

410
00:24:42,857 --> 00:24:44,108
[Josh sighs]

411
00:24:47,153 --> 00:24:48,154
[sighs]

412
00:24:55,536 --> 00:24:56,746
Handcuff knot.

413
00:24:59,665 --> 00:25:01,499
- Hey.
- Hey.

414
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,834
[Josh] How's she doing?

415
00:25:02,835 --> 00:25:05,253
She's asleep.
I gave her two Xanax.

416
00:25:05,254 --> 00:25:07,547
Xanaxes? Xani?

417
00:25:07,548 --> 00:25:09,925
- Whatever, she's asleep.
- Okay, good. Good.

418
00:25:09,926 --> 00:25:11,469
[sighs] So...

419
00:25:12,970 --> 00:25:13,970
what do we do now?

420
00:25:13,971 --> 00:25:15,847
Uh, I mean,
the only thing we can do.

421
00:25:15,848 --> 00:25:18,225
We call the cops.
We tell them everything.

422
00:25:18,226 --> 00:25:19,434
Right, yeah.

423
00:25:19,435 --> 00:25:21,520
- Yeah.
- But what about...

424
00:25:22,855 --> 00:25:26,567
Well, uh, obviously
I'll need to, uh, you know.

425
00:25:27,777 --> 00:25:29,486
I just don't understand
how this could have happened.

426
00:25:29,487 --> 00:25:31,154
Don't they have safeguards
for this kind of shit?

427
00:25:31,155 --> 00:25:32,490
I have no idea.

428
00:25:33,032 --> 00:25:34,867
Like a glitch maybe?

429
00:25:35,618 --> 00:25:36,702
Yeah.

430
00:25:38,996 --> 00:25:41,874
Okay. Okay, so...

431
00:25:43,292 --> 00:25:45,168
I'll call the cops,
and you will...

432
00:25:45,169 --> 00:25:47,128
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah. Yeah.

433
00:25:47,129 --> 00:25:50,090
Sorry, do you mind,
um, taking it outside?

434
00:25:50,091 --> 00:25:53,678
Just 'cause...
I-- I wanna say goodbye.

435
00:25:55,930 --> 00:25:56,930
Yeah.

436
00:25:56,931 --> 00:25:58,641
- Yeah, buddy. Sure.
- Yeah, thanks.

437
00:26:08,734 --> 00:26:09,901
Iris, wake up.

438
00:26:09,902 --> 00:26:10,986
...be lost without you!

439
00:26:10,987 --> 00:26:13,613
Hey, hey, hey.
Hey, it's okay. You're okay.

440
00:26:13,614 --> 00:26:15,740
- You're okay. I'm here. Hey.
- [breathing shakily] Josh.

441
00:26:15,741 --> 00:26:17,325
- Listen to me.
- [breathing shakily]

442
00:26:17,326 --> 00:26:20,704
Wait. Why are my hands tied?
Why are my hands tied, Josh?

443
00:26:20,705 --> 00:26:23,081
Iris. We didn't have a choice.
We didn't have a choice.

444
00:26:23,082 --> 00:26:24,874
You murdered Sergey.
You remember?

445
00:26:24,875 --> 00:26:25,792
No, no, no, no.

446
00:26:25,793 --> 00:26:27,544
It was self-defense.
He was gonna kill me.

447
00:26:27,545 --> 00:26:29,587
He was gonna kill me.
You gotta believe me.

448
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:31,172
No, I believe you, Iris.

449
00:26:31,173 --> 00:26:33,009
I mean, you couldn't lie to me
even if you wanted to.

450
00:26:33,718 --> 00:26:34,718
What?

451
00:26:34,719 --> 00:26:38,180
It's, um,
part of your programming.

452
00:26:39,056 --> 00:26:41,559
Programming? What the hell
are you talking about?

453
00:26:42,101 --> 00:26:43,101
[Iris breathes shakily]

454
00:26:43,102 --> 00:26:44,561
Okay, um...

455
00:26:44,562 --> 00:26:46,980
Sorry, there's just
no delicate way to say this.

456
00:26:46,981 --> 00:26:51,067
So, I'm just gonna
rip the Band-Aid right off.

457
00:26:51,068 --> 00:26:52,986
[Iris breathing shakily]

458
00:26:52,987 --> 00:26:54,405
You're a robot.

459
00:26:57,616 --> 00:26:58,616
I'm...

460
00:26:58,617 --> 00:26:59,994
A robot.

461
00:27:01,662 --> 00:27:06,208
More specifically,
you're a companion robot.

462
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:10,086
A companion robot?

463
00:27:10,087 --> 00:27:12,006
Yeah, it's like a, um...

464
00:27:12,965 --> 00:27:15,717
[sighs]
I hate the word "fuckbot."

465
00:27:15,718 --> 00:27:18,512
Um, 'cause you do so much more
than that, but, uh...

466
00:27:19,805 --> 00:27:22,350
You're an
emotional support robot...

467
00:27:23,684 --> 00:27:24,852
that fucks.

468
00:27:26,604 --> 00:27:27,687
You're joking, right?

469
00:27:27,688 --> 00:27:29,689
- This is just a sick--
- Iris, what's the weather?

470
00:27:29,690 --> 00:27:30,774
It's currently 72 degrees

471
00:27:30,775 --> 00:27:33,194
with an 83% chance
of rain in the evening.

472
00:27:37,448 --> 00:27:38,281
- Are--
- Hmm.

473
00:27:38,282 --> 00:27:40,116
Are you still not convinced?

474
00:27:40,117 --> 00:27:41,827
Yeah, okay, uh...

475
00:27:43,079 --> 00:27:44,120
Let's see.

476
00:27:44,121 --> 00:27:45,955
Iris, do you know
any foreign languages?

477
00:27:45,956 --> 00:27:48,458
Can you speak, say, Spanish?

478
00:27:48,459 --> 00:27:50,961
Josh, you know
<i>no sé hablar español</i>.

479
00:27:52,505 --> 00:27:53,505
<i>¿Qué?</i>

480
00:27:53,506 --> 00:27:55,340
- How about Chinese?
- [speaking Spanish]

481
00:27:55,341 --> 00:27:57,509
[speaking Mandarin]

482
00:27:57,510 --> 00:27:58,676
Do I need to keep going?

483
00:27:58,677 --> 00:28:00,178
'Cause I can go, uh...

484
00:28:00,179 --> 00:28:02,514
I can do Portuguese.
I can do Korean.

485
00:28:02,515 --> 00:28:03,766
I can do, uh...

486
00:28:04,850 --> 00:28:07,352
I don't know what Telugu is,
but apparently you speak it.

487
00:28:07,353 --> 00:28:09,230
I don't-- I don't understand.

488
00:28:09,772 --> 00:28:10,939
I--

489
00:28:10,940 --> 00:28:12,399
No, no, no. I have memories.

490
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:15,944
Uh, uh... College.
Uh, summer jobs. I've--

491
00:28:15,945 --> 00:28:18,405
I've been to Japan. Twice.

492
00:28:18,406 --> 00:28:19,781
Okay, so what those are--

493
00:28:19,782 --> 00:28:20,865
Those are, um...

494
00:28:20,866 --> 00:28:23,284
They're like outlines
of memories.

495
00:28:23,285 --> 00:28:26,871
You know, just enough to give
you a little, uh, backstory.

496
00:28:26,872 --> 00:28:29,082
The-- The-- The day we met
in the grocery store.

497
00:28:29,083 --> 00:28:32,752
You and the oranges. That is
not an outline of a memory.

498
00:28:32,753 --> 00:28:34,629
Yeah, it's fake.
Never happened.

499
00:28:34,630 --> 00:28:35,713
I just randomly picked it

500
00:28:35,714 --> 00:28:37,132
from a drop-down list
of meet-cutes.

501
00:28:37,133 --> 00:28:39,843
It could've been anywhere.
It could've been dog park,

502
00:28:39,844 --> 00:28:43,013
a bookstore, farmer's market.

503
00:28:45,099 --> 00:28:46,392
It never happened?

504
00:28:47,518 --> 00:28:49,060
[sighs] Okay, do, um--

505
00:28:49,061 --> 00:28:51,981
Do you wanna know how we met?
Like, how we really met?

506
00:28:53,232 --> 00:28:54,733
["Iris" playing on speakers]

507
00:28:57,528 --> 00:28:59,321
Hey. Josh Beeman?

508
00:28:59,864 --> 00:29:01,656
- Yeah, that's me.
- Okay.

509
