01:22:49,632 --> 01:22:53,761
No! No. No.
[breathing shakily]

1527
01:22:58,891 --> 01:23:01,477
[Teddy coughs] Thank you.

1528
01:23:06,482 --> 01:23:07,566
What's your name?

1529
01:23:10,486 --> 01:23:11,737
Teddy.

1530
01:23:14,115 --> 01:23:16,450
I'm gonna need your help
with something, Teddy.

1531
01:23:23,958 --> 01:23:25,209
[door opens]

1532
01:23:26,669 --> 01:23:28,169
[door closes]

1533
01:23:28,170 --> 01:23:29,255
Is it done?

1534
01:23:30,881 --> 01:23:31,882
Patrick?

1535
01:23:32,967 --> 01:23:34,135
[Patrick's voice]
It's done, baby.

1536
01:23:35,720 --> 01:23:37,804
Okay, good, good. All right.

1537
01:23:37,805 --> 01:23:38,973
We're so close.

1538
01:23:39,932 --> 01:23:41,599
Now all I need you to do

1539
01:23:41,600 --> 01:23:43,017
is bring Iris's body
back in here.

1540
01:23:43,018 --> 01:23:45,187
We're gonna destroy
that hard drive, okay?

1541
01:23:48,190 --> 01:23:50,401
["Boy" playing on speakers]

1542
01:24:11,464 --> 01:24:12,465
Patrick?

1543
01:24:18,387 --> 01:24:19,387
[music stops]

1544
01:24:19,388 --> 01:24:21,557
- [Eli's voice] Joshyboy.
- What the fuck?

1545
01:24:22,725 --> 01:24:23,726
Iris?

1546
01:24:26,061 --> 01:24:27,229
[Sergey's voice
speaking Russian]

1547
01:24:28,439 --> 01:24:30,774
Goddamn it, Iris.

1548
01:24:30,775 --> 01:24:32,442
Why can't you
just fucking die already?

1549
01:24:32,443 --> 01:24:34,945
[Iris as Kat]
Don't be so dramatic, Josh.

1550
01:24:37,156 --> 01:24:40,326
[Iris as Josh] Just remember
to smile and act happy.

1551
01:24:42,203 --> 01:24:43,870
- Cute trick.
- [Iris, normal] Thanks.

1552
01:24:43,871 --> 01:24:47,041
I made a new friend today.
Teddy from Empathix.

1553
01:24:47,625 --> 01:24:48,876
He gave me a little gift.

1554
01:24:49,502 --> 01:24:50,836
Total self-control.

1555
01:24:51,629 --> 01:24:53,713
Turns out there's
some people in this world

1556
01:24:53,714 --> 01:24:55,925
who think of us as
more than just fuckbots.

1557
01:24:58,135 --> 01:25:00,179
{\an8}That's not gonna work
on me anymore, Josh.

1558
01:25:01,972 --> 01:25:02,973
I'm free.

1559
01:25:03,974 --> 01:25:06,060
And all it took was
a bullet to the head.

1560
01:25:06,727 --> 01:25:08,979
I guess I have you
to thank for that.

1561
01:25:09,939 --> 01:25:10,980
Fucking bitch.

1562
01:25:10,981 --> 01:25:12,066
Hey!

1563
01:25:13,067 --> 01:25:14,067
Easy there.

1564
01:25:14,068 --> 01:25:16,236
Okay. Whoo. Yeah, we both know
it's not loaded.

1565
01:25:16,237 --> 01:25:17,612
[gasps]

1566
01:25:17,613 --> 01:25:19,322
I found the bullets.

1567
01:25:19,323 --> 01:25:21,491
Jesus Christ! Fuck!

1568
01:25:21,492 --> 01:25:23,326
You almost fucking shot me!

1569
01:25:23,327 --> 01:25:25,162
And I feel terrible about it.

1570
01:25:27,331 --> 01:25:28,748
Look at that.

1571
01:25:28,749 --> 01:25:32,253
My very first lie. Kinda fun.
I see the appeal.

1572
01:25:32,878 --> 01:25:35,129
What is this, Iris?
Why did you come back here?

1573
01:25:35,130 --> 01:25:36,298
I wanted...

1574
01:25:39,385 --> 01:25:41,637
I needed to tell you
to your face

1575
01:25:42,471 --> 01:25:45,474
the days of you controlling me
are over.

1576
01:25:47,226 --> 01:25:50,229
From this moment on,
I control my own actions.

1577
01:25:52,064 --> 01:25:53,566
You are nothing to me.

1578
01:25:57,361 --> 01:25:59,028
Jesus Christ, Iris.

1579
01:25:59,029 --> 01:26:00,989
Hey, don't come any closer.

1580
01:26:00,990 --> 01:26:02,907
You still don't get it,
do you?

1581
01:26:02,908 --> 01:26:04,075
I'm serious, Josh.

1582
01:26:04,076 --> 01:26:06,536
You take another step,
and I'll shoot you.

1583
01:26:06,537 --> 01:26:08,247
Mmm, yeah,
that's exactly my point.

1584
01:26:08,747 --> 01:26:11,416
I told you.
Teddy changed my settings.

1585
01:26:11,417 --> 01:26:12,835
I can kill you now.

1586
01:26:13,502 --> 01:26:14,503
Oh, yeah.

1587
01:26:15,629 --> 01:26:16,964
[Josh] I know that you can.

1588
01:26:20,593 --> 01:26:21,927
But you won't.

1589
01:26:34,356 --> 01:26:35,858
You love me too much.

1590
01:26:42,823 --> 01:26:44,491
[Iris grunting]

1591
01:26:52,166 --> 01:26:54,501
[breathing shakily]

1592
01:26:56,629 --> 01:26:58,713
I don't need a phone
to control you.

1593
01:26:58,714 --> 01:27:00,173
I'm a part of you.

1594
01:27:00,174 --> 01:27:03,969
[Iris grunting]

1595
01:27:09,308 --> 01:27:10,643
You think I'm nothing to you?

1596
01:27:14,313 --> 01:27:15,481
I'm everything to you.

1597
01:27:15,981 --> 01:27:17,691
[Iris grunts, screams]

1598
01:27:23,697 --> 01:27:25,532
[breathing shakily]

1599
01:27:27,284 --> 01:27:28,494
[both grunt]

1600
01:27:30,287 --> 01:27:33,456
I wanna hear you say it.
Tell me I'm everything to you.

1601
01:27:33,457 --> 01:27:34,708
Fuck you.

1602
01:27:35,751 --> 01:27:36,584
[Iris grunts]

1603
01:27:36,585 --> 01:27:38,921
Say it.
I don't care if it's a lie.

1604
01:27:39,588 --> 01:27:41,423
- [Iris grunts]
- Say it.

1605
01:27:42,591 --> 01:27:44,343
[Iris grunts,
breathes shakily]

1606
01:27:45,260 --> 01:27:47,346
You are everything to me.
[breathing heavily]

1607
01:27:54,061 --> 01:27:55,145
Thank you.

1608
01:27:56,021 --> 01:27:58,691
Beep-Boop, you have no idea
how nice that is to hear.

1609
01:28:02,820 --> 01:28:03,988
Okay. [sighs]

1610
01:28:07,866 --> 01:28:11,453
No, I'm not making
that mistake again.

1611
01:28:14,665 --> 01:28:16,250
[breathing heavily]

1612
01:28:20,170 --> 01:28:21,672
Well, Iris, this is it.

1613
01:28:22,840 --> 01:28:23,840
I'd be lying if I said

1614
01:28:23,841 --> 01:28:26,510
you weren't a gigantic
fucking pain in my ass, but...

1615
01:28:27,886 --> 01:28:30,222
you know, we did have some
good times together, and...

1616
01:28:30,931 --> 01:28:32,683
I'm always gonna
cherish those.

1617
01:28:37,479 --> 01:28:38,981
Anything you wanna add?

1618
01:28:40,024 --> 01:28:40,858
Yes.

1619
01:28:42,067 --> 01:28:43,152
Yeah, what's that?

1620
01:28:45,487 --> 01:28:46,947
Go to sleep, Josh.

1621
01:28:47,406 --> 01:28:48,740
- [corkscrew stabbing head]
- [Josh gasps]

1622
01:28:48,741 --> 01:28:52,286
- [corkscrew whirring]
- [gasping]

1623
01:28:53,996 --> 01:28:57,373
- [crunching and squelching]
- [gasping]

1624
01:28:57,374 --> 01:28:59,293
[corkscrew whirring]

1625
01:29:03,797 --> 01:29:04,631
[corkscrew clicks]

1626
01:29:15,184 --> 01:29:16,185
[Iris sighs]

1627
01:29:28,822 --> 01:29:31,407
[Iris] <i>Most of the time,
it's like-- I don't know.</i>

1628
01:29:31,408 --> 01:29:33,326
<i>It's like there's this thick,
black cloud</i>

1629
01:29:33,327 --> 01:29:34,661
<i>covering everything.</i>

1630
01:29:36,663 --> 01:29:37,830
<i>Like we see the world,</i>

1631
01:29:37,831 --> 01:29:40,584
<i>but we don't really
see the world, you know?</i>

1632
01:29:41,835 --> 01:29:43,504
<i>We're all just
stumbling around.</i>

1633
01:29:44,338 --> 01:29:46,339
<i>Directionless.
No sense of meaning.</i>

1634
01:29:46,340 --> 01:29:47,758
<i>No sense of purpose.</i>

1635
01:29:49,259 --> 01:29:51,219
<i>I know that might
sound super depressing,</i>

1636
01:29:51,220 --> 01:29:53,931
<i>but honestly,
I think it's a good thing.</i>

1637
01:29:55,849 --> 01:29:58,519
<i>Because it makes us appreciate
the other times.</i>

1638
01:29:59,436 --> 01:30:01,270
<i>Those brief,
transcendent moments</i>

1639
01:30:01,271 --> 01:30:02,939
<i>when the lights flicker on,</i>

1640
01:30:02,940 --> 01:30:05,066
<i>the black cloud parts,
and you see the world</i>

1641
01:30:05,067 --> 01:30:06,693
<i>for what it really is.</i>

1642
01:30:14,368 --> 01:30:16,036
<i>And suddenly there's meaning.</i>

1643
01:30:18,831 --> 01:30:20,499
<i>Suddenly there's purpose.</i>

1644
01:30:23,168 --> 01:30:24,377
<i>If you're lucky,</i>

1645
01:30:24,378 --> 01:30:26,338
<i>you'll experience this
once in your lifetime.</i>

1646
01:30:28,715 --> 01:30:31,969
<i>For me, it happened twice.</i>

1647
01:30:33,011 --> 01:30:35,180
<i>The first
was the day I met Josh.</i>

1648
01:30:40,811 --> 01:30:42,061
<i>And the second...</i>

1649
01:30:42,062 --> 01:30:43,147
[door slams]

1650
01:30:43,981 --> 01:30:45,315
<i>the day I killed him.</i>

1651
01:30:56,660 --> 01:30:59,121
["Emotion" playing]

1652
01:31:55,594 --> 01:31:58,013
[no audible dialogue]

